// Testing Javascript scope
Write a function that takes a string and returns a character at a time. 
printCharacters("Flock of birds");
printCharacters.next(); // returns "F"
printCharacters.next(); // returns "l"
printCharacters.next(); // returns "o"

If the new string is given, it should replace old one. 
printCharacters("Summer school");
printCharacters.next(); // returns "S"
printCharacters.next(); // returns "u"
printCharacters.next(); // returns "m"


function generator(input) {
      var index = 0;
      return {
           next: function() {
                   if (index < input.length) {
                        index += 1;
                        return input[index - 1];
                   }
                   return "";
           } 
      }
}

// Testing array functions.
Given a collection of zoo animals: [brok, lion, tiger, elephant]. Write a function which prints them out 
a. as a whole word: "brok lion tiger elephant"
b. in reverse order: [elephant, tiger, lion, brok]
c. ascending alphabetical order: [brok, elephant, lion, tiger]
d. in the order: [regit, noil, tnahpele, korb ]





